# Graphs Workspace Architecture Map

This document explains the signal flow and connections between modules in the **Graphs Workspace** using the MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel) pattern.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "View Layer"
        VWG[VWorkspaceGraphs<br/>Main Workspace View]
        VGraph[VGraph<br/>Plot Widget Component]
        VDialog[CustomizeGraphDialog<br/>Settings Dialog]
    end
    
    subgraph "ViewModel Layer"
        VM[VMWorkspaceGraphs<br/>Business Logic]
    end
    
    subgraph "Model Layer"
        MGraph[MGraph<br/>Graph Data Model]
    end
    
    VWG -->|"creates & manages"| VGraph
    VWG -->|"opens"| VDialog
    VWG -->|"calls methods"| VM
    VM -->|"emits signals"| VWG
    VM -->|"creates/updates"| MGraph
    VDialog -->|"modifies"| VGraph
    VDialog -.->|"triggers refresh"| VGraph
    
    style VWG fill:#e1f5ff
    style VGraph fill:#e1f5ff
    style VDialog fill:#e1f5ff
    style VM fill:#fff4e1
    style MGraph fill:#f0f0f0
```

## Module Responsibilities

### üìä **MGraph** (Model)
**File:** [m_graph.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py)

**Purpose:** Pure data container for graph properties

**Key Properties:**
- [graph_id](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#323-326), `df_name` - Graph identification
- `x`, `y`, `y2`, `y3`, `z` - Axis mappings
- [plot_style](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#598-609) - Plot type (scatter, line, box, etc.)
- `dpi`, `xmin`, `xmax`, `ymin`, `ymax` - Display settings
- [annotations](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/customize_graph_dialog.py#375-392) - List of annotation objects
- [axis_breaks](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/customize_graph_dialog.py#393-434) - Axis break configurations
- [legend_properties](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#236-276) - Custom legend settings

**No Logic:** Just stores data, no business logic

---

### üé® **VGraph** (View Component)
**File:** [v_graph.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py)

**Purpose:** Matplotlib-based plotting widget

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Renders plots using matplotlib
- Manages figure, axes, and canvas
- Handles mouse events (dragging annotations)
- Applies visual styling (colors, markers, labels)

**Key Methods:**
- [plot(df)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#1224-1265) - Main rendering method
- [create_plot_widget(dpi)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#121-172) - Creates matplotlib canvas
- [_plot_primary_axis()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#378-458) - Plots on main Y-axis
- [_apply_axis_breaks()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#1055-1205) - Renders axis breaks
- [_render_annotations()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#829-845) - Draws annotations

**Data Flow:** Receives DataFrame ‚Üí Renders plot ‚Üí Emits no signals (pure visualization)

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è **CustomizeGraphDialog** (View Component)
**File:** [customize_graph_dialog.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/customize_graph_dialog.py)

**Purpose:** Non-modal dialog for customizing graph appearance

**Key Features:**
- **Annotations Tab:** Add/edit/delete text and line annotations
- **Legend Tab:** Customize legend colors, markers, labels
- **Axis Tab:** Configure axis breaks (X and Y)

**Key Methods:**
- [_refresh_plot()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/customize_graph_dialog.py#369-374) - Lightweight visual refresh (doesn't update model)
- [_apply_axis_breaks()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#1055-1205) - Applies axis break settings
- `_on_annotation_added()` - Adds new annotation to graph

**Important:** Directly modifies [VGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#22-889) widget properties, does NOT update the ViewModel/Model

---

### üè¢ **VWorkspaceGraphs** (View)
**File:** [v_workspace_graphs.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py)

**Purpose:** Main workspace UI orchestrator

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Manages MDI subwindows (multiple graphs)
- Handles toolbar interactions
- Syncs GUI ‚Üî ViewModel
- Manages graph lifecycle (create/update/delete)

**Key Methods:**
- [_on_add_plot()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#748-762) - Creates new graph
- [_on_update_plot()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#836-894) - Updates existing graph (full rebuild)
- [_collect_plot_config()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1300-1340) - Gathers GUI inputs
- [_configure_graph_from_model()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1341-1400) - Applies model properties to VGraph
- [save_workspace()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1495-1511) - Syncs VGraph state back to model

**Data Structure:**
```python
self.graph_widgets = {
    graph_id: (VGraph, data, QMdiSubWindow)
}
```

---

### üß† **VMWorkspaceGraphs** (ViewModel)
**File:** [vm_workspace_graphs.py](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py)

**Purpose:** Business logic and state management

**Key Responsibilities:**
- Manages graph models ([MGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py#7-159) instances)
- Applies data filters
- Handles workspace save/load
- Emits signals to notify View of changes

**Key Methods:**
- [create_graph(config)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#307-322) - Creates [MGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py#7-159), returns [graph_id](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#323-326)
- [update_graph(graph_id, config)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#331-340) - Updates existing [MGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py#7-159)
- [get_graph(graph_id)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#327-330) - Retrieves [MGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py#7-159)
- [apply_filters(df_name, filters)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#214-232) - Filters DataFrame
- [save_workspace(path)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1495-1511) - Saves all graphs to `.graphs` file
- [load_workspace(path)](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1474-1504) - Loads graphs from file

**Signals:**
- `graph_created` - Emitted when new graph is created
- `graph_updated` - Emitted when graph is modified
- `workspace_loaded` - Emitted when workspace file is loaded

