## Key Design Patterns

### ‚úÖ MVVM Pattern Compliance

| Layer | Responsibilities | Dependencies |
|-------|-----------------|--------------|
| **Model** ([MGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/model/m_graph.py#7-159)) | Pure data storage | None |
| **ViewModel** ([VMWorkspaceGraphs](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/viewmodel/vm_workspace_graphs.py#21-449)) | Business logic, state management | Model only |
| **View** ([VWorkspaceGraphs](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#22-1525), [VGraph](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/v_graph.py#22-889)) | UI presentation | ViewModel + Model (read-only) |

### ‚ö†Ô∏è Architecture Note: CustomizeGraphDialog

[CustomizeGraphDialog](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/components/customize_graph_dialog.py#14-560) is a **special case** that breaks strict MVVM:
- **Why:** Performance - avoids full plot rebuild for visual tweaks
- **How:** Directly modifies `VGraph.annotations` and `VGraph.axis_breaks`
- **Sync:** Changes are synced back to model during [save_workspace()](file:///c:/Users/VL251876/Documents/Python/SPECTROview-1/spectroview/view/v_workspace_graphs.py#1495-1511)

**Trade-off:** Better UX (instant visual feedback) vs. architectural purity

